'''Yî-kâ''' (儒家) he [[Khûng-chṳ́ ]] sṳ̂-sióng cho-vì chú-yeu nui-yùng ke yit-chak [[chet-ho̍k]] sṳ̂-sióng thí-hì, kì-yu ham-cho '''Yî-kau''' fe̍t chá '''Khûng-kau'''. Yî-kâ chet-ho̍k sia̍p-khi̍p chṳn-chhṳ, tho-tet, [[sa-fi]], to [[Tûng-â]] kok-koet chṳ̂-chûng hó-yû yáng-hióng-li̍t.

==Li̍t-sṳ́ ==
Yî-kâ ke li̍t-sṳ́  cho-tet tûi-sok to [[Chhûn-chhiû Sṳ̀ -thoi]], yù Khûng-chṳ́  chhóng li̍p. Khûng-chṳ́  yî-chhièn chên-kîn cho-ko kôn, ngièn-kiu chhut yit-tho lî-lun hiong kok-koet thûi-siau, than-he m̀ sṳ̀n-kûng. Heu-lòi [[Chan-koet Sṳ̀ -thoi]], [[Men-chṳ́ ]] yu chiông Yî-kâ kói-liòng, chai sṳ̀n-vì sîn yit-tho lî-lun hi thûi-siau, kiet-kó yit-ngióng phàng-ngìn lî. 
Yî-kâ chhai [[Hon-chêu]] chṳ̂-chhièn pin m̀ su-to chhùng-sṳ, chhṳ̍t-to [[Hon Vú-ti]]  "Pa-thut Pak-kâ, Thu̍k-chûn Yî-su̍t" (罷黜百家，獨尊儒術), Yî-kâ chhiu sṳ̀n-vì chûng-koet ho̍k-su̍t sṳ̂-sióng ke chhùng-sîm. 


